With the Style attribute, you can fully customize the Visual Presentation of the Web page.
Styles like color, size, formatting and more.
Color:
     Change the color of text using style attribute.
     <p style="color:green">Color is Changed</p>
The Style attribute can be use define properties like color, font size and alignment.
You can customize the multiple property at the same time.
Just seperate each property:value seperate with semicolon (;).
<p style="color:green; text-align:center">Style Text</p>.
border property has 3 sub-parts like 1.border-width:2px,  2.border-style:solid and 3.border-color:red.

code:
     <!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Style Attribute</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1 style="color:red;font-size:25px;text-align:center">Style Attribute</h1>
    <p style="background-color:azure;color:black;text-align:left">Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur adipisicing elit. Nostrum rem laboriosam sunt quam fugit est numquam expedita odit facilis harum similique assumenda explicabo et beatae, laudantium praesentium autem labore minus?</p>
    <button style="border:2px dotted red;background-color: rgb(83, 54, 17);color:rgb(118, 101, 115);font-size: 20px;">Submit</button>
</body>
</html>
